  "response": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "trade": "Permit & Testing",
        "lines": [
          "Pull city roofing permit",
          "Test existing roofing/underlayment for asbestos before tear-off (per South Coast AQMD Rule 1403)",
          "Confirm Cool Roof (Title 24 CRRC) compliance for the new shingle product before ordering material"
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Demo / Tear-Off",
        "lines": [
          "Tarp landscaping, protect gutters, and stage debris chute/dumpster",
          "Demo complete roof: tear off old shingles, underlayment, and flashing down to the deck",
          "Inspect the deck and fix all damaged wood on roof surface",
          "Schedule and pass deck/nailing inspection before covering with underlayment"
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Roofing Installation",
        "lines": [
          "Install synthetic waterproof underlayment (30-lb synthetic/black paper), with self-adhered ice-and-water membrane at eaves and valleys",
          "Install new drip edge at eaves and rakes",
          "Install all new flashing, including step and valley flashing at all walls, chimneys, and roof-to-wall transitions",
          "Replace all metal cover vents; replace/install new vents per code",
          "Install new 30-year composition shingles per manufacturer's nailing pattern and exposure, starting from the eave; brand and color chosen by customer",
          "Install ridge vent, pipe boots, and all penetration flashing details",
          "Seal all around vents and penetrations with lifetime silicone"
        ]
      },
      {
        "trade": "Final Inspection & Clean Up",
        "lines": [
          "Schedule final roofing inspection",
          "Magnetic nail sweep of entire property, including driveway and adjacent walkways",
          "Clean entire job site and haul away all debris"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "notes": [
      "Assumed existing roof is a single layer (standard tear-off/reroof); if a second layer is found underneath, code caps over-layers at 2 max and full tear-off is already the correct scope here regardless.",
      "Deck repair is written as a standard inspect-and-fix line per the roofing playbook; actual extent of rotted/undersided sheathing (if any) won't be known until tear-off exposes the deck."
    ],
